Tibetan herders are being forced to settle in towns by China, disrupting their traditional way of life.
The government's relocation program aims to combat desertification caused by overgrazing and urban sprawl.
Guizhou Province is particularly affected by stone desertification, threatening farmers' livelihoods.
Sandstorms are a growing concern, with Minqin County experiencing severe erosion.
China is taking steps to reverse soil erosion, banning farming on steep hillsides and promoting terracing.
Efforts have led to increased grain production and improved livelihoods for millions.
Xinjiang is a hotspot for soil erosion, with deserts expanding due to human activities.
